edu.umaryland.igs.idea
Interface CustomRenderable

All Known Implementing Classes:
LikelihoodData
public interface CustomRenderable

The CustomRenderable interface is implemented by classes whose objects can be converted to an AWT or Swing component designed to take up part of a table cell. This component is added to the table cell renderer's rendering of that cell. It is intended that objects of CustomRenderable classes be added directly to the data structure that serves as the table's model. Each CustomRenderable class should define a toString() method that returns a reasonable value suitable for displaying as a label in the cell in which the custom rendering is to be displayed.
